Full Update Workflow Summary

To update the remote repository:

1. Get latest changes: git pull

2.  Add your files: git add . #adds all new or modified files | git add (file name) #adds the speficic file

3.  Commit your changes: git commit -m "A brief description of my changes"

4.  Send your changes: git push






Claude commands

PERMISSIONS
You can start a session with bypassPermissions mode using a command-line flag:

  claude --dangerously-skip-permissions

  Or alternatively:

  claude --permission-mode bypassPermissions

  Both of these will skip all permission prompts for just that session without changing your permanent settings. The session-specific flag overrides any settings in your config files and only applies to that one session.

FILE USAGE IN PROMPTING
‚óè Here are the ways you can provide files to me in Claude Code:

  Quick Methods

  1. Use the @ symbol (easiest):
  @/path/to/document.pdf - add some text to this
  Or with relative paths:
  @./document.pdf - add a header to this

  2. Drag and drop:
  - Simply drag a file into the Claude Code terminal window

  3. Copy and paste:
  - Copy a file and paste it with Ctrl+V (Windows/Linux)

  4. Just mention the file path:
  Read this PDF and add text: C:\Users\morte\Documents\myfile.pdf

  For PDFs Specifically

  I can read PDFs directly using my Read tool. Once you reference a PDF file (using any method above), I can:
  - Extract and analyze the text content
  - Help you create modified versions
  - Generate new files with added text

  For example, you could say:
  @C:\Users\morte\Documents\report.pdf - add a title page with "Annual Report 2025"

  The @ symbol method is usually the most convenient for interactive sessions.